cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.ET 

This paper is about optimizing the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for high-throughput inference on FPGAs. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the use of a confidence evaluation unit, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper presents a toolflow for optimizing the CNN model, which could be classified under cs.ET (Emerging Technologies).
